                  <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName>
               </persName>
                  <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
                  <faith type="EOTC"/>
                  <occupation type="ecclesiastic">saint</occupation>
               <birth> He was born at <placeName ref="LOC1236Agama">ʾAgāma</placeName>
               </birth>
               <residence>
                  <placeName ref="LOC3653GundaG">Gunda Gunde</placeName>
               </residence>
               <floruit> He was  a saint of  15th to early 16th century and a follower of ʾabbā <persName ref="PRS3894estifano">ʾƎsṭifānos</persName>. 
                  Since there was a shortage of priests following the persecution of the <persName ref="PRS11211Stephanites">Stephanites</persName> by King <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>, 
                  he was chosen by  ʾabbā  <persName ref="PRS1008Abakaraz">ʾAbakarazun</persName>, 
                  the head of the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC3653GundaG">Gunda Gunde</placeName>
                  to go to <placeName ref="wd:Q1218">Jerusalem</placeName> in <date>1476</date>.
                     
                  </floruit>
